cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM 

The paper deals with computational complexity of finding equilibria in games and fixed points of monotone functions, which are central topics in game theory and computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves analysis of algorithms and lower bounds, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of boolean circuits and local search algorithms indicates a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), respectively. Finally, the study of monotone functions on grids suggests a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
